Database Documentation
PolyLife - Microservice 9
1. UserProfile

Purpose

Stores users' physical profile information received from the Core Authentication service.
| Field         | Type        | Description                         |
| ------------- | ----------- | ----------------------------------- |
| id            | SERIAL      | Primary Key                         |
| core_user_id  | INTEGER     | User ID received from Core (Unique) |
| age           | INTEGER     | User age                            |
| height        | FLOAT       | Height (cm)                         |
| weight        | FLOAT       | Weight (kg)                         |
| fitness_level | VARCHAR(20) | User fitness level                  |
| created_at    | TIMESTAMP   | Creation time                       |
| updated_at    | TIMESTAMP   | Last update time                    |

2. FitnessGoal

Purpose

Stores predefined fitness goals
| Field       | Type         | Description      |
| ----------- | ------------ | ---------------- |
| id          | SERIAL       | Primary Key      |
| name        | VARCHAR(100) | Goal name        |
| description | TEXT         | Goal description |
| created_at  | TIMESTAMP    | Creation time    |

3. UserGoal

Purpose

Maps users to their fitness goals.
| Field   | Type    | Description      |
| ------- | ------- | ---------------- |
| id      | SERIAL  | Primary Key      |
| user_id | INTEGER | FK → UserProfile |
| goal_id | INTEGER | FK → FitnessGoal |
UNIQUE(user_id, goal_id)

4. WorkoutPreference

Purpose

Stores each user's workout preferences.
| Field          | Type         | Description               |
| -------------- | ------------ | ------------------------- |
| id             | SERIAL       | Primary Key               |
| user_id        | INTEGER      | FK → UserProfile (Unique) |
| workout_type   | VARCHAR(100) | Preferred workout type    |
| available_days | JSONB        | Available workout days    |
| equipment      | JSONB        | Available equipment       |
| preferred_time | TIME         | Preferred workout time    |

5. TrainingGroup

Purpose

Stores training groups suggested to users.
| Field            | Type         | Description         |
| ---------------- | ------------ | ------------------- |
| id               | SERIAL       | Primary Key         |
| name             | VARCHAR(100) | Group name          |
| description      | TEXT         | Group description   |
| workout_type     | VARCHAR(100) | Workout category    |
| difficulty_level | VARCHAR(30)  | Difficulty level    |
| goal_id          | INTEGER      | FK → FitnessGoal    |
| available_days   | JSONB        | Training days       |
| equipment        | JSONB        | Required equipment  |
| max_members      | INTEGER      | Maximum members     |
| start_time       | TIME         | Training start time |
| end_time         | TIME         | Training end time   |
| created_at       | TIMESTAMP    | Creation time       |

CHECK(max_members > 0)

CHECK(end_time > start_time)

6. GroupMembership

Purpose

Stores membership information of users in training groups.
| Field     | Type        | Description        |
| --------- | ----------- | ------------------ |
| id        | SERIAL      | Primary Key        |
| user_id   | INTEGER     | FK → UserProfile   |
| group_id  | INTEGER     | FK → TrainingGroup |
| joined_at | TIMESTAMP   | Join date          |
| status    | VARCHAR(20) | Membership status  |
Default

Active

Constraint

UNIQUE(user_id, group_id)

7. Exercise

Purpose

Stores exercises used by training groups.
| Field      | Type         | Description       |
| ---------- | ------------ | ----------------- |
| id         | SERIAL       | Primary Key       |
| name       | VARCHAR(100) | Exercise name     |
| type       | VARCHAR(50)  | Exercise category |
| difficulty | VARCHAR(30)  | Difficulty        |
| risk_level | VARCHAR(30)  | Risk level        |

8. GroupExercise

Purpose

Maps exercises to training groups.
| Field       | Type        | Description        |
| ----------- | ----------- | ------------------ |
| id          | SERIAL      | Primary Key        |
| group_id    | INTEGER     | FK → TrainingGroup |
| exercise_id | INTEGER     | FK → Exercise      |
| intensity   | VARCHAR(30) | Exercise intensity |
UNIQUE(group_id, exercise_id)

9. InjuryHistory

Purpose

Stores users' injury history.
| Field       | Type         | Description        |
| ----------- | ------------ | ------------------ |
| id          | SERIAL       | Primary Key        |
| user_id     | INTEGER      | FK → UserProfile   |
| injury_type | VARCHAR(100) | Injury type        |
| body_part   | VARCHAR(100) | Affected body part |
| severity    | VARCHAR(30)  | Injury severity    |
| injury_date | DATE         | Date of injury     |
| notes       | TEXT         | Additional notes   |

10. RiskAnalysis

Purpose

Stores injury risk analysis results.
| Field          | Type        | Description        |
| -------------- | ----------- | ------------------ |
| id             | SERIAL      | Primary Key        |
| user_id        | INTEGER     | FK → UserProfile   |
| group_id       | INTEGER     | FK → TrainingGroup |
| risk_level     | VARCHAR(30) | Risk level         |
| score          | INTEGER     | Risk score         |
| recommendation | TEXT        | Recommended action |
| created_at     | TIMESTAMP   | Analysis date      |

Relationships
UserProfile (1) -------- (1) WorkoutPreference

UserProfile (1) -------- (N) UserGoal -------- (1) FitnessGoal

FitnessGoal (1) -------- (N) TrainingGroup

UserProfile (1) -------- (N) GroupMembership -------- (1) TrainingGroup

TrainingGroup (1) ------ (N) GroupExercise ------ (1) Exercise

UserProfile (1) -------- (N) InjuryHistory

UserProfile (1) -------- (N) RiskAnalysis -------- (1) TrainingGroup

Constraints Summary
Primary Key on all tables.
Foreign Keys maintain referential integrity.
WorkoutPreference.user_id is unique (One-to-One).
UserGoal(user_id, goal_id) is unique.
GroupMembership(user_id, group_id) is unique.
GroupExercise(group_id, exercise_id) is unique.
TrainingGroup.max_members > 0.
TrainingGroup.end_time > start_time.
Default membership status is Active.